The paper deals with a scheduling problem with constraints, which is a classic topic in computer science. The problem is related to bin packing, knapsack, and cardinality constraint variants, which are all in the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the structure of optimal solutions, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
